</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E67FFEBFF3F76E2DA81F93B" blockId="21.[192,1440,1480,1728]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="B95344267E67FFEBFF3F76E2DE53FA1B" bold="true" box="[192,333,1480,1504]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Definition.</emphasis>
A sister genus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E67FFEBFDEA76E2DC5DFA1A" authority="Butler, [1870]" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1870" box="[533,835,1480,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E67FFEBFDEA76E2DD82FA1B" box="[533,668,1480,1504]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Ceratrichia</emphasis>
Butler, [1870]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E67FFEBFCB076E3DC9CFA1A" box="[847,898,1481,1505]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E67FFEBFC1F76E2DA5BFA1A" authority="Fabricius, 1787" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1787" box="[992,1349,1480,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nothus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E67FFEBFC1F76E2DB97FA1B" box="[992,1161,1480,1504]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Papilio nothus</emphasis>
Fabricius, 1787
</taxonomicName>
), where these species were formerly placed, but separated from it by a prominent genetic distance consistent with how other genera are defined (
<figureCitation id="131C84B17E67FFEBFDDA7522DD77F9DA" box="[549,617,1544,1569]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="22.[192,275,1419,1441]" captionTargetBox="[193,1440,215,1384]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[192,1440,213,1385]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figure 9. Genomic trees of Astictopterini and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677253/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Keys to VI.31.B in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E67FFEBFCA87523DCEDF9DA" author="Evans" box="[855,1011,1545,1569]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" refId="ref27329" refString="Evans, W. H. 1937. A catalogue of the African Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum. British Museum (Natural History); London. xii + 212 p., 30 pl." type="book" year="1937">Evans (1937)</bibRefCitation>
and differs from its relatives by pale apical spot on ventral hindwing in cell R 
<subScript id="17A39A717E67FFEBFD5F751DDDB6F9BE" attach="left" box="[672,680,1591,1605]" fontSize="6" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">5</subScript>
-M 
<subScript id="17A39A717E67FFEBFD367512DDCCF9BD" attach="left" box="[713,722,1592,1606]" fontSize="6" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">1</subScript>
is in line with the spots in cells next to it (not offset strongly basad); uncus bulbous in ventral view, which gives tegumen with uncus a bowling duckpin shape; harpe widening distad, separated from ampulla; ventral hindwing ochreous with many small silvery spots, dorsal forewing brown with large orange-yellow spots. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly669.9.1:A231G, aly214.13.5:A98G, aly4389.5.1:G869A, aly 
<date id="FF99BEF47E67FFEBFC137582DB7DF93B" box="[1004,1123,1704,1728]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" value="1329-04-13">1329.4.13</date>
: 
<specimenCode id="DB81304F7E67FFEBFB987582DBB8F93B" box="[1127,1190,1704,1728]" collectionCode="T" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">T479</specimenCode>
C, aly214.13.5:A97C.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33DCBBF7E67FFEBFF3F75FCDDD2F870" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9898347E67FFEBFF3F75FCDA8FF8F5" blockId="21.[192,1440,1750,1806]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="B95344267E67FFEBFF3F75FCDE45F915" bold="true" box="[192,347,1750,1774]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a feminine noun in the nominative singular, a fusion of the Latin words 
<emphasis id="B95344267E67FFEBFF3F75DCDFF3F8F6" box="[192,237,1782,1805]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Arg</emphasis>
[entum] (silver) and [g] 
<emphasis id="B95344267E67FFEBFDF775DCDD4CF8F6" box="[520,594,1782,1805]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">emma</emphasis>
(jewel), for the shiny, silvery gem-like spots on the hindwing below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E67FFEBFF3F7409DB2EF8A0" blockId="21.[192,1440,1827,1883]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="B95344267E67FFEBFF3F7409DEB0F8C0" bold="true" box="[192,430,1827,1851]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Species included.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="549C26967E67FFEBFE17740EDD03F8C7" box="[488,541,1828,1852]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E67FFEBFD7A7409DCE8F8C0" authority="Druce, 1910" authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1910" box="[645,1014,1827,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurea">
<emphasis id="B95344267E67FFEBFD7A7409DC42F8C1" box="[645,860,1827,1851]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Ceratrichia aurea</emphasis>
Druce, 1910
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E67FFEBFBFF7409DA82F8C0" authority="Miller, 1971" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1971" box="[1024,1436,1827,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maesseni">
<emphasis id="B95344267E67FFEBFBFF7409DA1EF8C1" box="[1024,1280,1827,1851]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Ceratrichia maesseni</emphasis>
Miller, 1971
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E67FFEBFF3F7469DD73F8A0" authority="Riley, 1925" authorityName="Riley" authorityYear="1925" box="[192,621,1859,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mabirensis">
<emphasis id="B95344267E67FFEBFF3F7469DEC7F8A0" box="[192,473,1859,1883]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Ceratrichia mabirensis</emphasis>
Riley, 1925
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E67FFEBFD517469DB32F8A0" authority="Evans, 1946" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1946" box="[686,1068,1859,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bonga">
<emphasis id="B95344267E67FFEBFD517469DC95F8A0" box="[686,907,1859,1883]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Ceratrichia bonga</emphasis>
Evans, 1946
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
